defaultClubs.name: Mockup Club
defaultClubs.description: Do you like making mockups of clubs? Then this is the club for you. The Mockup Club focuses on teaching members how to create their own mockups of clubs. Activities include coming up with clubs ideas and writing their own club descriptions such as this one. Pray you don't break everything. Contact a club admin for details.

defaultClubs.name: Accounting Club
defaultClubs.description: We the Accounting Club provides additional perspectives and supplemental information concerning public, private, and governmental accounting. Our main goal is to promote the professional and personal development of our members through socials, community service, professional interactions, workshops, and office tours. We continue to rank high among the largest student organizations and welcome students from all academic disciplines.

defaultClubs.name: AECT - Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: Our organization provides graduate students in the Learning Design & Technology Department with professional, social, and cultural support; a forum for discussion about student issues; and official representation to the UH Graduate Student Organization. It also serves alumni of the LTEC program with opportunities to stay in touch with the department.

defaultClubs.name: Aikido at UHM
defaultClubs.description: To practice Aikido

defaultClubs.name: AINAMOANA PHILOSOPHIES ORGANIZATION (APO) at the University of Hawai’i at Mānoa
defaultClubs.description:
To support a shared space for like-minded thinkers. The intended focus is those genealogies of thought which have their genesis in, and their identities tied to ʻĀina Moana(AM). 
APO seeks to create an academic space which will embrace AM philosophies. APO establishes a kauhale for those engaged in AM philosophies. It is a place where AM philosophies guide the space, language, and identities. A place to strengthen academic engagement amongst AM philosophers as well as a place from which AM philosophers may engage with the wider academic community and other organizations. APO seeks to distinguish and elevate those philosophical inquiries of specific concern to AM philosophers, which are often distinct from and unaddressed by academic institutions at the writing of this Constitution. The group was founded to investigate, understand, and perpetuate the philosophical views of the peoples of ʻĀina Moana in thought, speech, and action.

defaultClubs.name: Alohathon Dance Marathon
defaultClubs.description:
AlohaThon Dance Marathon at the University of Hawaiʻi
at Mānoa is the Aloha State's first and only Miracle
Network Dance Marathon (DM). It is a nationwide
movement held at over 400 college campuses in
support of Children's Miracle Network. In 2019, a total of
over $44 million was raised from DMs across the nation.
Since inception, Miracle Network Dance Marathon has
raised more than $400 million for kids across North
America- ensuring that no child or family fights
pediatric illness or injury alone.

Participants are challenged each year to raise funds
that culminate up to the 6-hour long main virtual event.
AlohaThon celebrates with non-stop dancing to fight
for the keiki of Hawaiʻi. All funds raised are donated to
our local Children's Miracle Network Hospital, Kapiolani
Medical Center for Women & Children.

defaultClubs.name: Alpha Gamma Delta Delta Sigma Chapter
defaultClubs.description:
To gain understanding that wisdom may be vouchsafed to me
To develop and prize health and vigor of body
To cultivate acquaintance with many whom I meet
To cherish friendships with but a chosen few and to study to perfecting of those friendships
To welcome the opportunity of contributing to the world's work in the community where i am placed because of the joy of service thereby bestowed and the talent of leadership multiplied
To honor my home, my country, my religious faith
To hold truth inviolable, sincerity essential, kindness invaluable
To covet beauty in environment, manner, word and thought
To possess high ideals and to attain somewhat unto them
This shall be my purpose, that those who know me may esteem Alpha Gamma Delta for her attainments, revere her for her purposes, and love her for her womanhood.

defaultClubs.name: Alpha Sigma Phi
defaultClubs.description: Alpha Sigma Phi is not interested in only becoming the fraternity of choice, for this perspective unnecessarily narrows our recruitment efforts to those inclined to go Greek. We instead, will be focused on appealing to a broader base of undergraduate men, thereby competing directly with other activities and organizations on today's campuses. By so doing, help to attract the very best and brightest undergraduate men.

defaultClubs.name: Alpha Omega Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: Alpha Omega Hawaii provides students with the opportunity to grow spiritually through interaction with other students who are Christians at UH, while encouraging academic wellness and professional development.

defaultClubs.name: AMA/HMA Student Chapter at JABSOM
defaultClubs.description: The AMA/HMA Student Chapter at JABSOM serves the students of the Medical School and the broader University of Hawai‘i at Manoa community as an organization whose primary focus is on healthcare advocacy and policy. Nationally (through AMA) and regionally (through HMA), we advocate for policies that ensure access to quality medical care, strengthen public health, and protect the welfare of our future patients.

defaultClubs.name: American Association of University Women at UH Manoa
defaultClubs.description: The mission of our RIO is to promote the values of AAUW on the UHM campus and in the community; we are working towards equality in society by providing the tools necessary for women to gain economic security, to pursue their education, and advocate for women's rights.

defaultClubs.name: American Society of Civil Engineers
defaultClubs.description: The mission of the ASCE student chapter at the University of Hawai'i at Manoa is to expand the knowledge of aspiring civil engineers through networking, monthly meetings, socials, fundraisers and community service.

defaultClubs.name: Anakbayan Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: As an integral part of the national democratic movement of the Philippines the mission and purpose of Anakbayan-USA is to gather the broadest possible political, moral, material and sectoral support for Anakbayan Philippines and the national democratic struggle of the Filipino people.

defaultClubs.name: Animal Science Club
defaultClubs.description: The Animal Science Club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa is committed to students who share an interest and passion for animals and livestock production systems. The club accomplishes its mission by organizing events that emphasize education and hands-on experience. The club also participates in community service events.

defaultClubs.name: Anthropology Undergraduate Student Association
defaultClubs.description: AUSA is a student-led organization that provides undergraduate majors and non-majors with opportunities to: (1) learn more about anthropology (2) participate in networking events for students with interests in anthropology (3) participate in community service events (4) find out about field school, grants, fellowships, and research opportunities of interest to anthropology students.

defaultClubs.name: American Institute of Architecture Students - Hawaii Chapter
defaultClubs.description: The American Institute of Architecture Students (AIAS) is an independent, nonprofit, student-run organization dedicated to providing unmatched progressive programs, information, and resources on issues critical to architecture and the experience of education. The AIAS aims to promote excellence in architectural education, training, and practice; to foster an appreciation of architecture and related disciplines; to enrich communities in a spirit of collaboration; and to organize students and combine their efforts to advance the art and science of architecture.

defaultClubs.name: American Marketing Association at University of Hawaii at Manoa
defaultClubs.description: Provide its members with opportunities to grow socially, philanthropically, and professionally to prepare them for a smooth transition into the work environment.

defaultClubs.name: Anime Manga Society of Hawaii @ UH Manoa
defaultClubs.description: Provide a space for students who like anime and manga to gather, interact, and connect around a shared interest.

defaultClubs.name: Associated Students of the John A. Burns School of Medicine
Bachelor of Social Work Organization
defaultClubs.description: The BSWO was established to create a body responsive to the needs and desires of its constituents, provide for administrative continuity, and develop a responsible as well as critical awareness of prevalent attitude and actions through participation in co-curricular activities.

defaultClubs.name: Ballroom Dance Club at UH
defaultClubs.description: Promote both social and competitive ballroom dance

defaultClubs.name: Baptist Collegiate Ministries O'ahu
defaultClubs.description: BCM O'ahu exists to lead college students to an authentic and growing relationship with Jesus Christ that produces in them a passion for God, a desire to live holy, and a vision to impact their campuses and the world.

defaultClubs.name: Bedroom Artists and Musicians at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
defaultClubs.description: The purpose of our RIO is too create a network of students with similar interests in producing or recording music. This organization would also be a place to educate and guide those with no experience in such and would like to learn how to make music. Eventually I would like to organize our members into a collective of artists and producers that release music that talk about topics that are important to not only us as individuals but are important to the land and positively represent UH Manoa as a whole.

defaultClubs.name: Beta Alpha Psi - Delta Theta Chapter
defaultClubs.description: Beta Alpha Psi is the international honor organization for financial information students and professionals. The purpose of this organization shall be to instill in its members a desire for self-improvement, foster high moral and ethical standards in its members, encourage and give recognition to scholastic and professional excellence, cultivate a sense of responsibility and services in its members, promote the collegiate study of accounting, and provide opportunities for association among its members.

defaultClubs.name: Beta Beta Gamma
defaultClubs.description: To bring together a group of strong , caring women to create a sisterhood of leadership, community and diversity.

defaultClubs.name: Botanical Society of America Hawai'i Chapter
defaultClubs.description: The Botanical Society of America (“BSA”) Hawaiʻi Chapter (“Chapter”) shall be operated for scientific and educational purposes.

defaultClubs.name: Business Executive Society of Tomorrow
defaultClubs.description: The Business Executive Society of Tomorrow is a general business club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa’s Shidler College of Business. Founded by students in 1998, BEST has a proud history of maintaining and perpetuating excellence in its members. Through the years, we have developed a culture of diligence and dedication to personal and professional growth. Through a combination of tours, workshops, networking events, alumni events, community services, and socials, we strive to mold our members into well-rounded individuals. We pride ourselves in producing the business leaders of tomorrow, and we provide our members with ample opportunities to continually advance toward that goal.

defaultClubs.name: Chemistry Club at UH Manoa
defaultClubs.description: We strive to promote chemistry education and awareness in the local community.

defaultClubs.name: Chi Epsilon at UHM
defaultClubs.description: Chi Epsilon is a civil engineering honor society that invites top juniors and seniors to become a part of our club, where we do community service, professional development workshops, and fun social activities.

defaultClubs.name: Circle K International
defaultClubs.description: Circle K International is college and university students who are responsible citizens and leaders with a lifelong commitment to community service worldwide. Circle K inspires people to better our world. Its motto, the same as Kiwanis International’s, is “We Build.” Circle K provides constructive opportunities for students to become involved on their campuses and communities through service work to others in need. Circle K members have the chance to work with fellow students, children in the community, and other adults in need of special programs.

defaultClubs.name: Class of 2024 at JABSOM
defaultClubs.description:
Serve as liaisons between the larger student body and JABSOM faculty (e.g. Office of Medical Education and Office of Student Affairs).
Consult, deliberate, and make decisions for student-led events held at the John A. Burns School of Medicine (referred to as JABSOM from here on).
Fundraise and dispense funds for the purpose of class activities, academic opportunities, and other celebrations (ie. graduation).

defaultClubs.name: Class of 2025 at JABSOM
defaultClubs.description:
The purpose of this organization is to gather a group of students to:
1. Serve as liaisons between the larger student body and JABSOM faculty (e.g. Office of Medical Education and Office of Student Affairs).
2. Consult, deliberate, and make decisions for student-led events held at the John A. Burns School of Medicine (referred to as JABSOM from here on).
3. Fundraise and dispense funds for the purpose of class activities, academic opportunities, and other celebrations (i.e., graduation and senior lūʻau).

defaultClubs.name: Club Management Association of America
defaultClubs.description: The Club Managers Association of America is a professional association for students interested in working at membership/private clubs. We seek to promote relations between members and industry professionals, encourage education, and advance students’ professional lives through close engagement and partnership with local and international club industry professionals, as well as site inspections, seminars, and networking events.

defaultClubs.name: Coalition to Stop Campus Hunger
defaultClubs.description:
The purpose of the Coalition to Stop Campus Hunger at UH Mānoa is threefold:
2.1 To develop a sustainable community and institutional infrastructure necessary to improve food security for the UH Mānoa campus community.
2.2 To encourage all members of the UH Mānoa community to become involved in solving food insecurity issues on campus
2.3 To help to remove the social stigma that goes along with being food insecure.

defaultClubs.name: C.O.P. Alaka'ina
defaultClubs.description:
Our purpose is to promote college success and post-secondary opportunities for our College Opportunities Program (COP) students. COP Alaka'ina serves our COP freshmen and alumni throughout the academic year by providing guidance, information, and workshops about academic and college life at UH Manoa. Our areas of focus are the following: professional development, community service, socials, and fundraising.
As COP primarily serves those who are economically disadvantaged, academically underprepared, and those who come from underrepresented communities, every bit of support counts.

defaultClubs.name: CTAHR Student Ambassadors
defaultClubs.description: The purpose of this organization is to create awareness of CTAHR academic programs, recruit prospective students to the college, encourage student engagement, and to positively portray CTAHR to the University and outside communities.

defaultClubs.name: Delta Sigma Pi: Rho Chi
defaultClubs.description: Delta Sigma Pi is a professional fraternity organized to foster the study of business in universities; to encourage scholarship, social activity and the association of students for their mutual advancement by research and practice; to promote closer affiliation between the commercial world and students of commerce, and to further a higher standard of commercial ethics and culture and the civic and commercial welfare of the community.

defaultClubs.name: Disney Ohana Club
defaultClubs.description: To provide a safe environment for people to gather and share interests in Disney. Also to promote and encourage the Disney College Program and other Disney internship opportunities.

defaultClubs.name: Drone Technologies at the University of Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: DTUH is an interdisciplinary Vertically Integrated Project [VIP] consisting of various engineering majors such as Mechanical, Electrical, and Computer Engineering. VIP allows for the involvement of students from all undergraduate class standings (Freshman through Senior class standing). The purpose of DTUH is to expand the real-world applications of unmanned aerial systems [UAS], commonly referred to as drones. Every year, DTUH participates in the annual Association for Unmanned Vehicle Systems International Student Unmanned Aerial Systems [AUVSI SUAS] competition. The AUVSI SUAS competition provides a suitable environment for the advancement of Search and Rescue technologies of drones. The aim of DTUH is to provide undergraduate University of Hawaii Engineering students with unparalleled, extra-curricular educational opportunities in the cutting-edge field of drones.

defaultClubs.name: East-West Toastmasters
defaultClubs.description: To provide a mutually supportive and positive learning environment in which every member has the opportunity to develop communication and leadership skills, which in turn foster self-confidence and  personal growth

defaultClubs.name: Engineers' Council at the University of Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: The Engineers’ Council at the University of Hawaiʻi (ECUH) is a student-operated executive board, consisting of elected executive board (officer) positions, Affiliate College of Engineering (COE) Student Organization representatives, and a council member body. The mission of the ECUH is to provide unity action through cooperative, transparent, and effective representation of the student body of the COE at the University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa. By collaborating with students, faculty, affiliate student organizations, affiliate project organizations, and professional partners, the ECUH serves to promote academic, intellectual, cultural, and social understanding throughout the COE, and to provide students with the finest education environment possible.

defaultClubs.name: English Majors Association
defaultClubs.description: The purpose of this organization shall be to promote interaction amongst the students and faculty within the English Department, create an active literary community, and increase participation in both on-campus and off-campus English related events and activities. The English Majors Association will extend its membership opportunity once per semester to the entirety of the English major and minor in the hopes of increasing interconnectivity amongst students. With passion and dedication put forth towards the English discipline, the EMA will actively seek substantial opportunities for student involvement and recognition amongst peers and faculty. Increased participation and influence in the English department will be available to members of the EMA, as well as, an open-minded environment which values individual intellect, opinion, and creativity.

defaultClubs.name: Eta Kappa Nu
defaultClubs.description: Eta Kappa Nu is a professional Electrical and Computer Engineering honor society with its sole purpose being to promote academic excellence, professional accomplishments, and services for its members. Upon completion of the program, the students will be distinguished as having skills and character that is needed in the workforce.

defaultClubs.name: Every Nation Campus at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
defaultClubs.description: Every Nation Campus Ministries partners with schools to help students excel in their academics, develop leadership skills, be a positive influence in their community, and pursue a Christ-centered life.

defaultClubs.name: Ēwe ‘Ula
defaultClubs.description:
Nurses are among the front-line health workers that provide the time and hands on care for their patients.  Native Hawaiian Health has improved over the years  yet health disparities continue to exist.  Among the disparities are the small number of Native Hawaiian nurses.  Many institutions of education and health repeat non-indigenous values and practices which contribute to indigenous mis-trust and care confusion.  Cultural knowledge and cultural safety can change this. 
Ēwe ʻUla was created to provide a place for Native Hawaiian Nurses, and Kākoʻo (Allies of Native Hawaiian Health and the work of Native Hawaiian Nurses), to nurture, gather, support, and mentor one another.  The group was founded on the principle that creating a positive cultural identity will help nurses to bridge the gap between Western Nursing Education, Health Care and indigenous values for the patients they care for.

defaultClubs.name: Family Medicine Interest Group
defaultClubs.description: The Family Medicine Interest Group (FMIG) is a medical student-run organization that is advised by the Faculty Advisor, Dr. Jill Omori.  FMIG provides unique opportunities for medical students to learn about Family Medicine and to be involved with the community.

defaultClubs.name: Financial Management Association
defaultClubs.description: The Financial Management Association at Shidler College of Business prepares its members for the business world. We provide many opportunities for our members, in which they may apply to in the finance sector. The club continues to hold its values and beliefs for the next generation of leaders.

defaultClubs.name: Food Science and Human Nutrition Council
defaultClubs.description: Share news and volunteer opportunities relating to General food and nutrition with attending students. Organized club for students in majors relating to food and nutrition or those who are interested.

defaultClubs.name: Formula SAE Rainbow Warrior Racing
defaultClubs.description: Formula SAE is an international competition, in which students from universities design a Formula One-style racecar. The Rainbow Warrior Racing (RWR) Team's objective this year is to improve on and advance the design of the electric Formula racecar from last year with the goal to attend the competition and represent the University of Hawai’i at Manoa. Our mission as an organization is to provide our members with experiences that no course can replace, and develop them as engineers and people. The RWR team is a part of a senior design course, but the organization is also open to underclassmen members, which will give them an opportunity to expand their knowledge and improve the program in future years.

defaultClubs.name: Generation Action at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
defaultClubs.description: Generation Action at UHM exists to promote health rights, racial equity & intersectionality within the UH community. We support full access to comprehensive reproductive healthcare, educational programs that enhance understanding of human sexuality, as well as the public policies that support and guarantee access to these rights and services.

defaultClubs.name: Graduate Hui Ola Pono
defaultClubs.description: The Hui provides a space for public health students to present the ideas, interests, and concerns of the members of the student body and serves as a liaison between the students, faculty, and administration. The Hui facilitates communication and involvement among students through scheduled meetings, coordination of social and educational activities, and dissemination of necessary information. The Hui is an organization that provides students with opportunities to promote Public Health within both the university and Hawaiʻi community at large through outreach, education, and fundraising. Another facet of the group is to provide support and guidance for incoming students and link students in the Public Health program with other students and Public Health professionals locally, nationally, and internationally.

defaultClubs.name: Graduate Business Student Association
defaultClubs.description: The Graduate Business Student Association (GBSA) is a student organization that is made up of Shidler College of Business graduate students. The purpose of GBSA is to organize professional, social and community service events that spark lasting relationships within its member community. Although GBSA is heavily integrated with the Shidler College of Business, it is in no way a structural component, and is merely a student entity. All opinions of GBSA, reflect only the opinions of its board members and are not representative of the Shidler College of Business, nor the University of Hawaii at Manoa.

defaultClubs.name: Grey Hats at UHM
defaultClubs.description: Grey Hats aims to teach any students interested in Cybersecurity the fundamentals by working through various challenges, giving talks about a variety of tools and practical skills, and bringing in security professionals to talk about their career or job/internship opportunities.

defaultClubs.name: Hawaii Alpha Chapter of Pi Gamma Mu
defaultClubs.description: To encourage and recognize superior scholarship in social science disciplines and to foster cooperation and social service among its members. Pi Gamma Mu serves the various social science disciplines which seek to understand and explain human behavior and social relationships as well as their related problems and issues.

defaultClubs.name: Hawaii Chapter of the Society for Conservation Biology
defaultClubs.description: To educate the public and the UH community about Hawaii conservation issues and to engage them in conservation work.

defaultClubs.name: Hawaii Streams and Ecosystems
defaultClubs.description: The purpose of the Hawaii Streams and Ecosystems Organization is to educate, understand, and continuously explore streams throughout Hawaii. We hope to gain and spread more knowledge about the biological and cultural importance of Hawaii's streams and the benefits they provide, and promote awareness as to why stream conservation is vital in Hawaii.

defaultClubs.name: Hawaii Student Entrepreneurs
defaultClubs.description: To inspire students to be entrepreneurs and to help students start and grow businesses

defaultClubs.name: Hawaii Undergraduate Initiative
defaultClubs.description: Hawaii Undergraduate Initiative (HUI) strives to help incoming freshmen students smoothly transition into UH Mānoa, be part of a supportive community on campus, and provide leadership opportunities.

defaultClubs.name: Hillel Hawaii
defaultClubs.description: A resource for students interested in Judaism in Hawaii to connect to local congregations and their traditions.

defaultClubs.name: HOSA at UHM
defaultClubs.description: The primary purpose of HOSA at UHM is to serve the needs of its members and strengthen the Health Science Education (HSE)-HOSA Partnership.

defaultClubs.name: Hui Kākoʻo: Department of Social Work Graduate Student Organization
defaultClubs.description: To represent and advocate for Graduate Social Work students' interests and needs to the school administration and plan events and programs that promote community, professional development, and critical awareness of local and global issues.

defaultClubs.name: Hui Ola Pono
defaultClubs.description: Hui Ola Pono's purpose is to provide students with opportunities to promote Public Health within the community at large through outreach, education, and fundraising. Hui Ola Pono facilitates communication and involvement among students through scheduled meetings, coordination of social and educational activities, and dissemination of necessary information. We provide support and guidance for incoming students and link students in the Public Health program with other students and Public Health professionals. Our vision is to provide a sanctuary for public health undergraduate students to foster professional skills and meaningful connections for their future public health careers.
